AN ACT relating to jurisdiction; authorizing a court of this State to
exercise general personal jurisdiction over certain
business entities under certain circumstances; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes a court of this State to exercise jurisdiction over a party
2 to a civil action on any basis not inconsistent with the Nevada Constitution or
3 United States Constitution. (NRS 14.065) Section 1 of this bill authorizes a court of
4 this State to exercise general personal jurisdiction over certain business entities on
5 the sole basis that the business entity: (1) is organized, registered or qualified to do
6 business pursuant to the laws of this State; (2) expressly consents to the
7 jurisdiction; or (3) has certain contact with the State. Section 2 of this bill provides
8 that the amendatory provisions of section 1 apply to an action commenced on or
9 after October 1, 2025.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 14 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. A court of this State may exercise general personal
4 jurisdiction over a corporation, miscellaneous organization
5 described in chapter 81 of NRS, limited-liability company, limited-
6 liability partnership, limited partnership, limited-liability limited
7 partnership, business trust or municipal corporation created and
8 existing under the laws of this State, any other state, territory or
9 foreign government or the Government of the United States on the
